label.value: ligand-gated ion channel signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by activation of a ligand-gated ion channel on the surface of a cell. The pathway begins with binding of an extracellular ligand to a ligand-gated ion channel and ends with a molecular function that directly regulates a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label.value: basic amino acid transmembrane transport

value.value: The directed movement of basic amino acids from one side of a membrane to the other.

label.value: adaptive thermogenesis

value.value: The regulated production of heat in response to short term environmental changes, such as stress, diet or reduced temperature.

label.value: vacuolar localization

value.value: Any process in which the vacuole is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within the cell.

label.value: acinar cell proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of acinar cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. An acinar cell is a secretory cell that is grouped together with other cells of the same type to form grape-shaped clusters known as acini (singular acinus).

label.value: vascular associated smooth muscle cell proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of vascular smooth muscle cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. A vascular smooth muscle cell is a non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the blood vessels.

label.value: ribonucleoprotein complex

value.value: A macromolecular complex that contains both RNA and protein molecules.

label.value: ooplasm

value.value: The cytoplasm of an ovum.

label.value: hepatic stellate cell proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of hepatic stellate cells, resulting in the expansion of a hepatic stellate cell population. Hepatic stellate cells are found in the perisinusoidal space of the liver, and are capable of multiple roles including storage of retinol, presentation of antigen to T cells (including CD1d-restricted NKT cells), and upon activation, production of extracellular matrix components. This cell type comprises approximately 8-15% of total cells in the liver.

label.value: eosinophil homeostasis

value.value: The process of regulating the proliferation and elimination of eosinophils such that the total number of eosinophils within a whole or part of an organism is stable over time in the absence of an outside stimulus.

label.value: basophil homeostasis

value.value: The process of regulating the proliferation and elimination of basophils such that the total number of basophils within a whole or part of an organism is stable over time in the absence of an outside stimulus.
